    <title type="text">Call for Papers: Open Library of the Humanities (OLH) Journal</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a
      href="https://www.openlibhums.org/2014/12/02/olh-opens-for-submissions/">Open Library of the
      Humanities (OLH) Journal</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><img
      alt="https://www.openlibhums.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/OLH-WebsiteLogo-PNG.png"
      class="decoded"
      src="https://www.openlibhums.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/OLH-WebsiteLogo-PNG.png"
      />&nbsp;</blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><div style="text-align:
      justify;"> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><span>We are very pleased to
      announce that the OLH is now <a href="https://submit.openlibhums.org/"
      target="_blank">open for submissions</a> to its new&nbsp;megajournal, which covers
      the humanities disciplines.&nbsp;The submission platform, <a
      href="http://ubiquitypress.tumblr.com/post/104064465916/open-library-of-humanities-submission-system"
      target="_blank">developed by Ubiquity Press</a>, is based upon PKP's excellent <a
      href="https://pkp.sfu.ca/ojs/" target="_blank">Open Journal Systems</a>, but has been
      extensively modified to accommodate the editorial flow that is needed in a highly-distributed,
      large-scale system. We intend to release the source code for these modifications under an open
      license in the near future.</span></span></div><div style="text-align:
      justify;"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><span>&nbsp;</span></span></div><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"></span><div style="text-align: justify;"> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="line-height: 22.4px;">The OLH Editorial Team
      is made up of a network of leading academics from the international scholarly community, with
      <a href="https://submit.openlibhums.org/about/editorialTeam" target="_blank">Section
      Editors</a> covering all of the humanities disciplines,
      including:</span></span></div><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"></span><ul><li style="text-align: justify;"> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><span>History</span></span> </li><li
      style="text-align: justify;"> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><span>Theology
      &amp; Religious Studies</span></span> </li><li style="text-align:
      justify;"> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><span>Literature &amp;
      Languages</span></span> </li><li style="text-align: justify;"> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><span>Modern &amp; Ancient
      Languages</span></span> </li><li style="text-align: justify;"> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><span>Philosophy</span></span>
      </li><li style="text-align: justify;"> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><span>Cultural Studies &amp; Critical Theory</span></span>
      </li><li style="text-align: justify;"> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><span>Film, TV &amp; Media Studies</span></span>
      </li><li style="text-align: justify;"> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><span>Musicology, Drama &amp; Performance</span></span>
      </li><li style="text-align: justify;"> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><span>Classics</span></span> </li><li
      style="text-align: justify;"> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><span>Art,
      Design &amp; Art History</span></span> </li><li style="text-align:
      justify;"> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><span>Legal
      Theory</span></span> </li><li style="text-align: justify;"> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><span>Digital Humanities</span></span>
      </li><li style="text-align: justify;"> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><span>Politics &amp; Political Theory</span></span>
      </li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;"></span><div
      style="text-align: justify;"> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><span>We are
      also pleased to say that negotiations on the set of initial journals that will share an economy
      of scale and our economic model are well underway. More announcements on this front will be
      forthcoming in the near future.&nbsp;In the meantime, we would ask those who pledged
      articles to now begin to submit your work! We are aiming for a launch next year between May and
      Summer 2015. Thank you for your ongoing support in the creation of an open research and
      dissemination ecosystem for the humanities!</span></span></div><div
      style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><span>&nbsp;</span></span></div><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"></span><div style="text-align: justify;"> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="https://submit.openlibhums.org/about/submissions"
      target="_blank"><span>CLICK HERE TO VIEW&nbsp;OUR SUBMISSIONS
      PLATFORM</span></a></span></div></blockquote><br
      />]]></content>
